			<ns0:name>jamesfen...@gmail.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/105008541472586726939/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">This bug is critical for general application performance.
Take an example of a usual graphic application, First, we have some image at user managed memory, to show the image on the browser, we need at least three copies:
1. image =&gt; ImageData
2. PaintImageData to copy to backstore
3. backstore to browser.
In the worst case that almost the whole screen needed to be updated, the performance is not acceptable. Remember, since the application is dynamic, we should not always use ReplaceContent since whole screen update is not often anyway.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2011-03-05T04:49:36.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2011-03-05T04:49:36.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:updates /><ns0:title>Comment 1 by jamesfen...@gmail.com</ns0:title><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=1477#c1" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><ns0:link href="https://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/1477/comments/full/1" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /></ns0:entry>